\section{Introduction}

This document presents the theoretical foundation and simulation-based validation of 
\textbf{Mnemophysics}—a field that explores how structured memory influences the evolution 
and interaction of physical, energetic, and cognitive systems.

By introducing memory fields as active agents of causality, we offer a cohesive framework that 
connects quantum coherence, atomic structure, emergent behavior, and cosmological formation 
through a single paradigm: \textit{memory as causality-in-action}.

\section{Core Concepts and Terminology}

\subsection{Mnemophysics}

Mnemophysics is the study of systems where interaction, change, and persistence are 
determined by the imprint and evolution of memory fields. These fields act as dynamic 
repositories of influence, shaping future outcomes based on past configurations.

\subsection{Key Variables}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{\(X_{\text{Will}}\)}: The directional vector of energy, force, or desire.
    \item \textbf{\(X_{\text{Mem}}\)}: A field representing the memory of a system.
    \item \textbf{\(Y\)}: A scalar expressing the emergent complexity level of a system.
    \item \textbf{Power (P)}: The actionable influence of a system, resulting from the 
          alignment of Will and Memory.
    \item \textbf{Frequency (F)}: The rhythm or consistency of manifestation.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Power-Frequency Equations}

\begin{align}
    P &= \frac{X_{\text{Will}} \cdot X_{\text{Mem}}^Y}
             {X_{\text{Will}} / X_{\text{Mem}}^Y} \\
    F &= \left(X_{\text{Will}} \cdot X_{\text{Mem}}^Y\right) 
         - \left(X_{\text{Will}} / X_{\text{Mem}}^Y\right)
\end{align}

These equations define how memory fields condition the effect of will within a system, 
resulting in structured influence across time.

